        {
            "title": "油價若升至100美元可能推高美國通脹,但持續性是關鍵,Barclays稱",
            "description": "<div class=\"atoms\"><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit max-w-full\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"410\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/yztcdWicAvWjMjT_21H1Rg--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTYwNg--/https://i-invdn-com.investing.com/news/indicatornews_5_M_1440048359.jpg\" width=\"650\"/></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">Investing.com — <a class=\"link\" data-i13n=\"sec:content-canvas;subsec:anchor_text;elm:context_link\" data-ylk=\"slk:Barclays;sec:content-canvas;subsec:anchor_text;elm:context_link;itc:0\" href=\"https://hk.finance.yahoo.com/tag/Barclays\">Barclays</a>分析師指出,油價若飆升至每桶100美元,短期內可能會推高美國整體通脹率,但長期影響將主要取決於價格維持高位的時間長短。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">該行表示,油價達到100美元\"無疑會在整體層面上造成通脹壓力\",但除非價格長期維持高位,否則對更廣泛通脹的二次效應將有限。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">Barclays估計,原油價格持續上漲10%可能在一至兩個月內為整體CPI增加約0.2個百分點,主要是通過汽油價格上漲的途徑。</p><div class=\"bg-toast-background -mx-5 -mt-2 mb-3 pb-3 md:-mx-0 lg:mx-auto lg:w-[300px] lg:pb-0\"><div class=\"text-px14 text-gandalf py-1 text-center leading-5\">廣告</div><div class=\"mx-auto text-center min-w-[300px] min-h-[250px]\" id=\"sda-inbody-fb0893bd-2514-3ce0-91cf-e0bf37ec769f-1-iframe\"><div class=\"bg-dirty-seagull text-px12 text-dolphin mx-auto hidden items-center justify-center only:flex w-[300px] h-[250px]\">廣告</div></div></div><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">然而,預計對核心通脹的傳導效應將較小且較慢,因為能源價格衝擊通常對整體價格的影響比對基礎通脹更為直接。</p><div class=\"recommendation-contents\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mb-2 h-[30px] w-[80px] rounded-lg\"></div><div class=\"no-scrollbar -mx-5 mb-5 flex overflow-hidden overflow-x-auto md:-mx-2 lg:mb-3.5\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mr-2 ml-5 h-[92px] w-[calc(85%-28px)] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg md:ml-2 md:w-[calc(85%-16px)] lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mx-2 h-[92px] w-[85%] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div></div></div><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">該行指出,對消費者通脹真正重要的是汽油價格而非原油本身,因為原油僅佔最終零售汽油價格的約一半,其餘部分由煉油和分銷構成。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">Barclays表示,汽油價格通常反映原油價格變動的50-60%,調整通常在兩至三週內發生。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">目前的情況也與2022年俄羅斯入侵烏克蘭後的油價飆升有所不同。當時,全球供應鏈已經緊張,各國政府正向經濟注入財政刺激,放大了通脹壓力。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">Barclays稱,如今宏觀背景較為疲軟,消費者支出降溫,美國勞動力市場出現更多閒置,且過去12個月中有11個月的通脹數據低於預期。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">在其基準展望下,Barclays預測到2026年12月,整體CPI將達到2.7%的年增率,核心CPI將達到2.8%,前提是油價不會長期維持高位。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">不過,該行警告稱,若油價長期接近100美元,可能會推動整體通脹在2026年底接近3%,如果通脹預期開始上升,可能會延遲聯準會的降息行動。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><br/></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><em>此文章由人工智能協助翻譯。更多資訊，請參閱我們的使用條款。</em></p></div>",
